Package: INCOMMON
Title: INCOMMON: Inference of Copy Number and Mutation Multiplicity in Oncology
Version: 0.1.0
Maintainer: Nicola Calonaci <nicola.calonaci@gmail.com>
Authors@R:
    c(person("Nicola", "Calonaci", , "nicola.calonaci@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2721-4888")),
    person("Giulio", "Caravagna", , "gcaravagn@gmail.com", role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4240-3265")))
Description: Implements the statistical model described in Calonaci et al.
    (2024) <doi:10.1101/2024.05.13.24307238> to infer the copy number and
    multiplicity of somatic mutations from tumour-only read count data.
    Mutations are classified as either Tier-1 (present in 100% of cells)
    without copy-number alterations (heterozygous mutant diploid), with loss
    of heterozygosity, copy-neutral loss of heterozygosity, amplification, or
    Tier-2 (subclonal or with high ploidy and low multiplicity), providing a
    fast genome-interpretation framework for large-scale tumour-only
    sequencing cohorts.
